      • createChannel

        @POST(value="channels/create")
Call<Channel> createChannel(@Query(value="endpoint")
                                                           String endpoint,
                                                           @Query(value="app")
                                                           String app,
                                                           @Query(value="appArgs")
                                                           String appArgs,
                                                           @Query(value="channelId")
                                                           String channelId,
                                                           @Query(value="otherChannelId")
                                                           String otherChannelId,
                                                           @Query(value="originator")
                                                           String originator,
                                                           @Query(value="formats")
                                                           String formats)
        Create channel.
        Parameters:
        endpoint - Endpoint for channel communication (required)
        app - Stasis Application to place channel into (required)
        appArgs - The application arguments to pass to the Stasis application provided by 'app'. Mutually exclusive with 'context', 'extension', 'priority', and 'label'. (optional)
        channelId - The unique id to assign the channel on creation. (optional)
        otherChannelId - The unique id to assign the second channel when using local channels. (optional)
        originator - Unique ID of the calling channel (optional)
        formats - The format name capability list to use if originator is not specified. Ex. \"ulaw,slin16\". Format names can be found with \"core show codecs\". (optional)
        Returns:
        Call<Channel>

        @POST(value="channels")
Call<Channel> originateChannel(@Query(value="endpoint")

                                                       String context,

                                                       String formats)
        Create a new channel (originate). The new channel is created immediately and a snapshot of it returned. If a Stasis application is provided it will be automatically subscribed to the originated channel for further events and updates.
        Parameters:
        endpoint - Endpoint to call. (required)
        extension - The extension to dial after the endpoint answers. Mutually exclusive with 'app'. (optional)
        context - The context to dial after the endpoint answers. If omitted, uses 'default'. Mutually exclusive with 'app'. (optional)
        priority - The priority to dial after the endpoint answers. If omitted, uses 1. Mutually exclusive with 'app'. (optional)
        label - The label to dial after the endpoint answers. Will supersede 'priority' if provided. Mutually exclusive with 'app'. (optional)
        app - The application that is subscribed to the originated channel. When the channel is answered, it will be passed to this Stasis application. Mutually exclusive with 'context', 'extension', 'priority', and 'label'. (optional)
        appArgs - The application arguments to pass to the Stasis application provided by 'app'. Mutually exclusive with 'context', 'extension', 'priority', and 'label'. (optional)
        callerId - CallerID to use when dialing the endpoint or extension. (optional)
        timeout - Timeout (in seconds) before giving up dialing, or -1 for no timeout. (optional, default to 30)
        variables - The \"variables\" key in the body object holds variable key/value pairs to set on the channel on creation. Other keys in the body object are interpreted as query parameters. Ex. { \"endpoint\": \"SIP/Alice\", \"variables\": { \"CALLERID(name)\": \"Alice\" } } (optional)
        channelId - The unique id to assign the channel on creation. (optional)
        otherChannelId - The unique id to assign the second channel when using local channels. (optional)
        originator - The unique id of the channel which is originating this one. (optional)
        formats - The format name capability list to use if originator is not specified. Ex. \"ulaw,slin16\". Format names can be found with \"core show codecs\". (optional)
        Returns:
        Call<Channel>
